cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and syntactic processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses recurrent neural networks as generative models. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses electrophysiological responses to naturalistic text. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for parsing and modeling human language processing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of beam search, which is a common technique in computer vision and pattern recognition.
